Based on the architecture design, write a clear implementation summary.

**System:** SeaChain MVP - Enterprise Seafood Traceability Platform
**Problem:** Seafood importers, processors, and retailers face a $700M+ annual compliance burden and mounting reputational risk from IUU fishing in their supply chains. NOAA's 2024 SIMP Action Plan proposes expanding traceability requirements from 13 to ALL species groups, while EU IUU enforcement is intensifyin
**Solution:** SeaChain (renamed from OceanTrace after trademark clearance) - An enterprise SaaS traceability-as-a-service platform that seafood buyers deploy across their supplier networks to achieve automated SIMP/IUU compliance and fraud prevention. Core capabilities: (1) Fisher Mobile App—subsidized by buyers,

**Tech Stack:**
{
  "frontend": {
    "framework": "React with Vite",
    "language": "TypeScript",
    "rationale": "React Native can share code with mobile app, TypeScript ensures type safety for complex compliance data models, Vite provides fast development experience"
  },
  "backend": {
    "framework": "FastAPI",
    "language": "Python",
    "rationale": "FastAPI offers async performance, automatic OpenAPI docs for API consumers, excellent data validation with Pydantic, and Python ecosystem for future ML/analytics features"
  },
  "database": {
    "primary": "PostgreSQL",
    "caching": "Redis",
    "rationale": "PostgreSQL for ACID compliance required for audit trails and regulatory data, JSONB support for flexible catch metadata, Redis for session management and offline sync queues"
  },
  "infrastructure": {
    "hosting": "AWS (ECS Fargate + RDS + S3)",
    "rationale": "Enterprise buyers require SOC2/HIPAA-ready infrastructure, AWS offers compliance certifications out-of-box, ECS Fargate eliminates server management, cost-effective at MVP scale"
  }
}

**Core Components:**
[
  {
    "name": "Fisher Mobile App (React Native)",
    "responsibility": "Offline-first catch data capture at point of harvest with GPS, timestamps, photos",
    "technology": "React Native with SQLite local storage, background GPS tracking",
    "key_features": [
      "Offline data capture with automatic sync when online",
      "GPS location verification with tamper detection",
      "Photo capture for species verification",
      "Simple form: vessel ID, species, quantity, catch method",
      "Data encryption at rest (AES-256)"
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "Buyer Dashboard (React Web App)",
    "responsibility": "Supply chain visibility, compliance report generation, supplier management",
    "technology": "React + TanStack Query + Recharts for data visualization",
    "key_features": [
      "Real-time supply chain map showing catch origins",
      "Automated SIMP/IUU compliance reports (PDF export)",
      "Supplier onboarding workflow with invite codes",
      "Traceability timeline view (catch \u2192 processing \u2192 delivery)",
      "Alert system for incomplete/suspicious data"
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "Traceability API (FastAPI)",
    "responsibility": "Core business logic for catch records, chain of custody, compliance validation",
    "technology": "FastAPI + SQLAlchemy ORM + Celery for async tasks",
    "key_features": [
      "RESTful API with JWT authentication (role-based: fisher/buyer/admin)",
      "Catch record CRUD with immutable audit log",
      "Chain of custody linking (catch \u2192 processor \u2192 retailer)",
      "SIMP compliance validation rules engine",
      "Batch data import for legacy systems (CSV)"
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "Document Storage Service",
    "responsibility": "Secure storage for catch certificates, vessel licenses, inspection photos",
    "technology": "AWS S3 with presigned URLs, image optimization with Sharp",
    "key_features": [
      "Encrypted document storage (S3 server-side encryption)",
      "Automatic image compression and thumbnail generation",
      "Time-limited download URLs for security",
      "Document versioning for audit compliance"
    ]
  },
  {
    "name": "Simplified Blockchain Ledger (PostgreSQL-based)",
    "responsibility": "Immutable audit trail for critical compliance events (MVP uses append-only DB table instead of full blockchain)",
    "technology": "PostgreSQL with cryptographic hashing (SHA-256 chain)",
    "key_features": [
      "Append-only ledger table with hash chain verification",
      "Cryptographic proof of data integrity for audits",
      "Event log: catch recorded, custody transferred, inspection passed",
      "Export to compliance-ready format for regulators"
    ]
  }
]

**API Structure:**
{
  "base_url": "/api/v1",
  "endpoints": [
    {
      "path": "/auth/login",
      "method": "POST",
      "purpose": "Authenticate user (fisher/buyer/admin), return JWT token"
    },
    {
      "path": "/catches",
      "method": "POST",
      "purpose": "Fisher submits new catch record with GPS, species, quantity, photos"
    },
    {
      "path": "/catches",
      "method": "GET",
      "purpose": "Buyer retrieves all catches from their supplier network (filtered by date/species/vessel)"
    },
    {
      "path": "/catches/{id}",
      "method": "GET",
      "purpose": "Get detailed catch record with full traceability chain and custody history"
    },
    {
      "path": "/custody/transfer",
      "method": "POST",
      "purpose": "Record custody transfer event between supply chain actors"
    },
    {
      "path": "/suppliers",
      "method": "POST",
      "purpose": "Buyer invites new supplier, generates invite code"
    },
    {
      "path": "/suppliers",
      "method": "GET",
      "purpose": "List all suppliers in buyer's network with status"
    },
    {
      "path": "/reports/simp",
      "method": "POST",
      "purpose": "Generate SIMP compliance report for date range, return PDF download URL"
    },
    {
      "path": "/supply-chain/map",
      "method": "GET",
      "purpose": "Get geospatial data for supply chain visualization on dashboard map"
    },
    {
      "path": "/documents/upload",
      "method": "POST",
      "purpose": "Upload catch certificate, vessel license, or inspection photo to S3"
    }
  ],
  "authentication": "JWT with role-based access control (RBAC) - roles: fisher, buyer_admin, buyer_viewer, system_admin"
}

**MVP Scope:**
- In Scope: ['Fisher mobile app with offline catch data capture (species, GPS, quantity, photos)', 'Buyer web dashboard with supply chain map and traceability timeline', 'Automated SIMP compliance report generation (PDF export)', 'Supplier onboarding and management', 'Chain of custody tracking with immutable audit trail', 'Basic fraud detection (GPS validation, data completeness alerts)']
- Out of Scope: ['Computer vision for automatic species identification', 'IoT sensor integration (temperature, humidity monitoring)', 'Full blockchain implementation (use hash chain in PostgreSQL for MVP)', 'Multi-language support (English only for MVP)', 'Advanced analytics and predictive risk scoring', 'Third-party integrations (ERP systems, customs platforms)', 'White-label branding for resellers', 'Real-time SMS/email alerts (batch daily summaries only)', 'Mobile app for processors/retailers (web-only for non-fishers in MVP)']

Write a 300-500 word implementation summary that explains:
1. The overall technical approach and why these technologies were chosen
2. How the core components work together
3. The key data flows and user journeys
4. Implementation priorities and suggested build order
5. Potential technical challenges and how to address them

Write in clear, professional prose. This is for a technical audience who will implement the MVP.
Output ONLY the summary text, no JSON or additional formatting.

